text: Euhyparpax is a genus of moths of the family Notodontidae, the prominents. The genus was erected by Edna Libby Beutenmüller in 1893. There are two species:Euhyparpax rosea. Invertebrate Abstracts. Arizona Game and Fish Department. *Euhyparpax amatame (Dyar, 1916) *Euhyparpax rosea Beutenmüller, 1893 ==References== Category:Notodontidae
